						               													<description>Albastini is a competitive trick-taking multiplayer card game which is originally from Tanzania, East Africa.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It can be played with 2 to 8 players individually or in teams of 2, 3, or 4 players (i.e. 2v2, 3v3, 2v2v2, 4v4, or 2v2v2v2).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 72 cards per deck (8 suits with 9 cards per suit) A=11pts; 7=10pts; K=4pts; J=3pts; Q=2pts; 3-6=0pts.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It typically takes 15+ mins to play but players can opt to play with only 4 of the suits for faster game play (this is typically only encouraged if 2 - 4 players are playing).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is played clockwise with one card per hand. Players start off with five cards and pick a card from the deck every time a hand is played starting with the winner of the last hand. The game ends after all cards within the deck have been played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The objective of the game is to get the highest number of points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A trump suit is randomly selected at the beginning of each game which can be used to dominate all other cards regardless of their point value.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first card played within each round determines the suit that is in play for that round. It can only be beaten if a higher value card within the same suit is played or any trump card. Players do not have to follow suit during each round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player (or team) with the highest number of points at the end of the game is declared the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
